race.comment: HEY DAISY (4) progressive mare who can go quickly through her grades this time in. Returned a solid set of figures when she sat on the speed and faded late to run second over 1000m at the Sunshine Coast. Strips fitter and can get the job done. THE ROOKIE (8) was rewarded for her consistency with a comfortable on-pace Super Maiden victory over 1000m at Ballina. Has further upside and gets every chance from the draw. MONACO FLYER (5) showed blistering early speed before folding up late with a tiring third over 1000m at Ballina. Regular rider hops back on and can overcome the wide draw. COSMIC TREASURE (7) resumes in a winnable contest with a host of gear changes. Now in the John Higgins yard and fitted with a trial placing over 808m at Coffs Harbour. Respect.
